reviews.review_text:
Kicks the soundboard's ass This is both an incredible recording and an incredible show.  One minor complaint - a cut in drums > space that can easily be fixed by patching in two minutes from the SBD (other AUD also cuts at the same place).  There are other sources here at LlaMA that are downloadable and have short SBD patches, so I don't think two minutes from D>S would rouse anyone's ire.

That said, this source is an amazing recording.  Thank you!  Five stars, one star off for the cut and the abrupt patch in Other One.

Maybe the first source to do some justice.... Just listened to the Cassidy, and it sounded spirited and alive.  The soundboard never did.  The soundboard after slipknot emphasizes all the vocals, and buries the musical conversation.  This source, although not the greatest audience source ever, may be the first to capture the essence of this show.  

Recall, this is a generally lackluster show, but those who attended all seem to praise it.  This recording may be our first glimpse into what made this night special.

smokin!! Oh Yeah! this is the source I had gotten a few days after these shows. This is a great fantastic recording. I had 3rd Row for these 2 shows and this night was one of my top five shows i had seen through 86-90. The energy that was crackling of that stage that night was matched by 25,000 fans yelling and cheering at some of the loudest levels i had heard in years. Jerry was "On" this entire night. In fact, the whole band this night were all "on" and playing at  there highest levels of musical conversation. I remember leaving the show and the looks on peoples faces where a look that you had just witnessed greatness,history and once in a lifetime show!!!!!!!!

This was a hot show I have seen hundreds of shows.  Nothing lackluster about this one.  The Other One > Dew was something else at the show.  I admit it does not come through as well on the recording, but the consensus among the people I was with was that it was impossible to top and no encore should have been played.  It stomped.
